[SN]TITLE[SN]
Girl airlifted to hospital after crash in Llangefni

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A young girl has been airlifted to hospital with serious injuries after being hit by a car on Anglesey.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Police were called to Corn Hir near Llangefni at about 15:45 GMT on Thursday after the girl was struck by a grey Seat.
"The pedestrian, accompanied by a parent, have been airlifted to hospital with serious injuries," said Sgt Emlyn Hughes of North Wales Police.
The girl was taken to Ysbyty Gwynedd in Bangor.
The B5109 Cildwrn Road was closed for several hours and has now re-opened following investigations.
